Yes, attaching the LGTM tool log: https://lgtm.com/logs/00d47310d3af018d3beb998f24e3df418c79cde7/lang:go

1. I see that the current language analysis for sonic-telemetry is Python and there is no lgtm configuration file, so I added a lgtm configuration file that specified to use go as the testing language.
2. Since go.mod requires sonic-mgmt-common, and specifies that it should be located in the parent directory, LGTM cannot install the sonic-mgmt-common repository in it's parent directory as that is not allowed. Which is why for the purposes of LGTM, I change that the sonic-mgmt-common should be in LGTM's current working directory which is /opt/src
3. We can verify that the build passes as we see it in the logs. In the analysis tab, we can also see the current warnings
